Note:
Go Parser - Recursive descent parser for Go programming language

This file provides complete parsing for Go source code into an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST).
Handles all Go syntax including packages, imports, types, functions, statements, and expressions.

Features:
- Package and import declarations
- Function and method declarations (with multiple returns)
- Type declarations (structs, interfaces, type aliases)
- Variable and constant declarations
- All Go statements (if, for, switch, select, defer, go, return, etc.)
- Complete expression parsing with operator precedence
- Go-specific features (channels, goroutines, defer, select)

Dependencies:
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/go/go_lexer.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/go/go_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Types
Note: ============================================================================

Constant GO_PROGRAM as Integer is 1
Constant GO_PACKAGE as Integer is 2
Constant GO_IMPORT as Integer is 3
Constant GO_FUNCTION as Integer is 4
Constant GO_METHOD as Integer is 5
Constant GO_TYPE_DECL as Integer is 6
Constant GO_VAR_DECL as Integer is 7
Constant GO_CONST_DECL as Integer is 8
Constant GO_STRUCT_TYPE as Integer is 9
Constant GO_INTERFACE_TYPE as Integer is 10
Constant GO_FIELD as Integer is 11
Constant GO_PARAMETER as Integer is 12
Constant GO_BLOCK as Integer is 13
Constant GO_IF_STMT as Integer is 14
Constant GO_FOR_STMT as Integer is 15
Constant GO_SWITCH_STMT as Integer is 16
Constant GO_SELECT_STMT as Integer is 17
Constant GO_CASE_CLAUSE as Integer is 18
Constant GO_RETURN_STMT as Integer is 19
Constant GO_BREAK_STMT as Integer is 20
Constant GO_CONTINUE_STMT as Integer is 21
Constant GO_FALLTHROUGH_STMT as Integer is 22
Constant GO_GOTO_STMT as Integer is 23
Constant GO_DEFER_STMT as Integer is 24
Constant GO_GO_STMT as Integer is 25
Constant GO_ASSIGN_STMT as Integer is 26
Constant GO_SHORT_VAR_DECL as Integer is 27
Constant GO_EXPR_STMT as Integer is 28
Constant GO_BINARY_EXPR as Integer is 29
Constant GO_UNARY_EXPR as Integer is 30
Constant GO_CALL_EXPR as Integer is 31
Constant GO_INDEX_EXPR as Integer is 32
Constant GO_SLICE_EXPR as Integer is 33
Constant GO_SELECTOR_EXPR as Integer is 34
Constant GO_TYPE_ASSERT_EXPR as Integer is 35
Constant GO_COMPOSITE_LIT as Integer is 36
Constant GO_FUNC_LIT as Integer is 37
Constant GO_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 38
Constant GO_LITERAL as Integer is 39
Constant GO_BASIC_TYPE as Integer is 40
Constant GO_POINTER_TYPE as Integer is 41
Constant GO_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 42
Constant GO_SLICE_TYPE as Integer is 43
Constant GO_MAP_TYPE as Integer is 44
Constant GO_CHAN_TYPE as Integer is 45
Constant GO_FUNC_TYPE as Integer is 46

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
AST node for the Go frontend. Every parse_* routine produces one or
more of these. The five-slot layout (type, name, value, children
list, attributes dict) is uniform across all node kinds, with kind-
specific meaning attached by GO_* constants stored in node_type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
40-byte record (5 x i64). Offset 0 node_type (GO_* constant), 8 name
(StringCore handle or 0), 16 value (StringCore or 0), 24 children
(List handle, allocated lazily by add_node_child), 32 attributes
(Dict handle, allocated lazily by set_node_attribute).
@End Implementation
Type called "GoNode":
    node_type as Integer        Note: Node type (GO_PROGRAM, GO_FUNCTION, etc.)
    name as Integer             Note: Node name (identifier, operator, etc.)
    value as Integer            Note: Node value (literal value, etc.)
    children as Integer         Note: List of child nodes
    attributes as Integer       Note: Dictionary of attributes
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parser state. Holds the borrowed lexer handle plus a cached
current_token (refreshed by advance_token so peek_token_type is O(1)
without re-calling the lexer). The has_error/error_message pair is
sticky: once an expect_token fails, has_error stays 1 and combinators
short-circuit.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
32-byte record (4 x i64). Offset 0 lexer, 8 current_token, 16
has_error (0/1), 24 error_message (StringCore handle or 0).
@End Implementation
Type called "GoParser":
    lexer as Integer            Note: Go lexer instance
    current_token as Integer    Note: Current token type
    has_error as Integer        Note: Error flag
    error_message as Integer    Note: Error message
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates a GoParser bound to the supplied lexer. Primes the cursor
by calling advance_token so peek_token_type works immediately after
return. Lexer is borrowed; caller is responsible for its lifetime.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Layout.allocate(32); OOM returns 0. Writes lexer (0), zero
current_token (8), zero has_error (16), zero error_message (24).
Calls advance_token to refresh current_token from the lexer.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_go_parser" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create Go parser with lexer

    Let parser_size be 32  Note: GoParser: 4 fields × 8 bytes
    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with parser_size

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, 0  Note: current_token = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 0  Note: has_error = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 0  Note: error_message = 0

    Note: Prime the parser with first token
    proc advance_token with parser

    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Releases the 32-byte parser record. The lexer is borrowed (not
owned) so it is NOT freed here; the error_message slot is also not
freed because the only sources of those strings are static keyword
literals passed into expect_token (no allocation).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null short-circuits with success. Otherwise Layout.deallocate.
Returns 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "destroy_go_parser" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy Go parser

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with parser
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocator for AST nodes. Zero-initialises children/attributes so
later passes can use 'slot == 0' as the "uninitialised" probe
without per-allocation resets. Each parse_* routine wraps this with
node-type-specific population.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Layout.allocate(40); OOM returns 0. Writes node_type at offset 0 and
zeros at offsets 8/16/24/32 (name, value, children, attributes).
@End Implementation
Process called "create_go_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create AST node

    Let node_size be 40  Note: GoNode: 5 fields × 8 bytes
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with node_size

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, 0  Note: name = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0  Note: value = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0  Note: children = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0  Note: attributes = null

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sets the node's name slot. Null-checks the node so callers can use
the result of create_go_node without explicit OOM tests.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null short-circuits to 0. Writes name to offset 8.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_node_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node name

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sets the node's value slot (for literal lexemes, operator strings,
etc.). Null-checks the node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null short-circuits to 0. Writes value to offset 16.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_node_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node value

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, value
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a child to a parent's children list, creating the list
lazily on first use. The lazy allocation keeps leaf nodes (literals,
identifiers, basic types) from carrying an unused empty List handle.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null parent or null child short-circuits to 0. Reads children slot
at offset 24. If 0, creates a new List via List.create with the
child as its sole entry and stores the handle. Otherwise appends
the child to the existing list. Returns 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "add_node_child" takes node as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add child node to node

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24

    If children is equal to 0:
        Let new_list be proc create from List
        proc list_append from List with new_list, child
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, new_list
        Return 1
    End If

    proc list_append from List with children, child
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sets a key->value entry in the node's attributes dict, creating the
dict lazily on first use. Attributes carry parser-derived metadata
(e.g. channel direction "send"/"receive") that does not fit the
fixed five-slot layout.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null node short-circuits to 0. Reads attributes (offset 32). If 0,
creates a fresh Dict via Dict.create and stores the handle. Then
calls Dict.set with (dict, key, value). Returns 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_node_attribute" takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set node attribute

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let attributes be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32

    If attributes is equal to 0:
        Let new_dict be proc create from Dict
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, new_dict
        Set attributes to new_dict
    End If

    proc set from Dict with attributes, key, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Drives one tick of the lexer forward and caches the resulting
token type on the parser. Returning the new type lets callers in
parse_* combinators advance-and-test in one line.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null parser short-circuits to 0. Calls Lexer.next_token(lexer) to
get the next type and writes it to offset 8. Returns the token type.
@End Implementation
Process called "advance_token" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let token_type be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, token_type

    Return token_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Read-only accessor for the cached current token type. Constant time
because the lexer is not re-invoked - advance_token already populated
the slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null short-circuits to 0. Reads offset 8.
@End Implementation
Process called "peek_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token type without advancing

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
    Return token_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bridges to the lexer's lexeme accessor so identifier/literal parses
can attach the raw text to AST nodes. The token type is cached on
the parser but the lexeme text lives on the lexer; this routine
fetches the current lexeme from the lexer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null short-circuits to 0. Reads lexer (offset 0) and calls
Lexer.get_token_lexeme. Returns the StringCore handle (borrowed
from lexer storage; AST nodes that retain it should copy it).
@End Implementation
Process called "peek_token_lexeme" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token lexeme without advancing

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let lexeme be proc get_token_lexeme from Lexer with lexer

    Return lexeme
End Process

@Reasoning:
Predicate for branching on the current token without consuming it.
Returns 1 on match, 0 otherwise. Used everywhere parse_* needs to
look-without-touch (e.g. distinguishing 'else if' from 'else { ... }').
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls peek_token_type. Returns 1 iff result equals expected_type;
else 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "check_token_type" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if current token matches expected type

    Let current_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If current_type is equal to expected_type:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Conditional consume: if the current token matches, advance past it
and return 1; otherwise leave the cursor in place and return 0. Used
where optional syntax is permitted (e.g. trailing comma in
parameter lists).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls check_token_type. On match, calls advance_token and returns 1.
Otherwise returns 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "match_token" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Match and consume token if it matches expected type

    Let matches be proc check_token_type with parser, expected_type

    If matches is equal to 1:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Match-or-error: like match_token but flips has_error and records the
diagnostic on mismatch. Used at every position where the grammar
mandates a specific token (e.g. closing ')' after parameter list).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls match_token. On match returns 1. On mismatch writes 1 to
has_error (offset 16) and the error_msg pointer to offset 24, then
returns 0. The error_msg argument is a static string literal supplied
by the caller; it is not copied or freed.
@End Implementation
Process called "expect_token" takes parser as Integer, expected_type as Integer, error_msg as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Expect and consume specific token type

    Let matches be proc match_token with parser, expected_type

    If matches is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 1  Note: has_error = 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, error_msg
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Type Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses any Go type expression, returning a typed AST node tagged
with the appropriate GO_*_TYPE constant. Handles all type-flavour
introducer tokens in a single dispatch: '*' (pointer), '['
(array/slice), 'map' (map), 'chan'/'<-' (channel), 'func' (function
type), 'struct'/'interface' (composite). Identifiers fall through
as basic types.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads peek_token_type. Branches:
  '*' -> consume; create GO_POINTER_TYPE; recurse parse_type for
         element_type; attach as child.
  '[' -> consume; peek next; ']' -> GO_SLICE_TYPE + element_type;
         else parse expression for size + ']' + element type ->
         GO_ARRAY_TYPE.
  'map' -> consume; GO_MAP_TYPE; expect '['; parse key type;
           expect ']'; parse value type; attach both as children.
  'chan' -> consume; GO_CHAN_TYPE; if next is '<-' attribute
            direction="send"; else "bidirectional"; recurse on
            element type.
  '<-' -> consume; expect 'chan'; GO_CHAN_TYPE with direction
          "receive"; element type child.
  'func' -> consume; GO_FUNC_TYPE; expect '('; parse_parameter_list;
            expect ')'; optionally parse return result list.
  'struct' -> consume; GO_STRUCT_TYPE; expect '{'; loop
              parse_struct_field until '}'.
  'interface' -> similar for GO_INTERFACE_TYPE / parse_interface_method.
  Default -> identifier or qualified.Name as GO_BASIC_TYPE.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse Go type expression

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Pointer type (*T)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let pointer_node be proc create_go_node with GO_POINTER_TYPE
        Let base_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with pointer_node, base_type
        Return pointer_node
    End If

    Note: Array type ([n]T)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        Note: Check for slice ([]T)
        If next_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let slice_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SLICE_TYPE
            Let element_type be proc parse_type with parser
            proc add_node_child with slice_node, element_type
            Return slice_node
        End If

        Note: Array with size ([n]T)
        Let array_node be proc create_go_node with GO_ARRAY_TYPE
        Let size_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with array_node, size_expr
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer, "Expected ']' after array size"
        Set element_type to proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with array_node, element_type
        Return array_node
    End If

    Note: Map type (map[K]V)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MAP from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let map_node be proc create_go_node with GO_MAP_TYPE
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer, "Expected '[' after 'map'"
        Let key_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with map_node, key_type
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer, "Expected ']' after map key type"
        Let value_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with map_node, value_type
        Return map_node
    End If

    Note: Channel type (chan T, <-chan T, chan<- T)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CHAN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let chan_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CHAN_TYPE
        Let next_token be proc peek_token_type with parser

        Note: Send-only channel (chan<- T)
        If next_token is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            proc set_node_attribute with chan_node, "direction", "send"

        Otherwise:
            proc set_node_attribute with chan_node, "direction", "bidirectional"
        End If

        Set element_type to proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with chan_node, element_type
        Return chan_node
    End If

    Note: Receive-only channel (<-chan T)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_CHAN from Lexer, "Expected 'chan' after '<-'"
        Set chan_node to proc create_go_node with GO_CHAN_TYPE
        proc set_node_attribute with chan_node, "direction", "receive"
        Set element_type to proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with chan_node, element_type
        Return chan_node
    End If

    Note: Function type (func(...) ...)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FUNC from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let func_type_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FUNC_TYPE
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after 'func'"
        Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
        proc add_node_child with func_type_node, params
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after parameters"

        Note: Check for return type(s)
        Set next_token to proc peek_token_type with parser
        If next_token is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            If next_token is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
                If next_token is not equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
                    Let return_type be proc parse_type_or_result_list with parser
                    proc add_node_child with func_type_node, return_type
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Return func_type_node
    End If

    Note: Struct type
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let struct_node be proc create_go_node with GO_STRUCT_TYPE
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' after 'struct'"

        Note: Parse fields
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let current_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If current_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let field be proc parse_struct_field with parser
            proc add_node_child with struct_node, field
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end struct"
        Return struct_node
    End If

    Note: Interface type
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTERFACE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let interface_node be proc create_go_node with GO_INTERFACE_TYPE
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' after 'interface'"

        Note: Parse methods
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Set current_type to proc peek_token_type with parser

            If current_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let method be proc parse_interface_method with parser
            proc add_node_child with interface_node, method
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end interface"
        Return interface_node
    End If

    Note: Basic type or type name (identifier)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let type_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let type_node be proc create_go_node with GO_BASIC_TYPE
        proc set_node_name with type_node, type_name
        Return type_node
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized type
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let inner_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after type"
        Return inner_type
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses either a single return type ('int', '*MyType') or a
parenthesised list of types/named results ('(a, b int, err error)').
Go's function return signature uses the same syntactic prefix in
both cases - the leading '(' disambiguates.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks. '(' -> consume, parse_parameter_list, expect ')'. Otherwise
parse_type and return the single-type node directly.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_or_result_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single type or multiple return types

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Multiple return types in parentheses
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let result_list be proc create_go_node with GO_PARAMETER
        proc set_node_name with result_list, "result_list"

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let current_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If current_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let param_type be proc parse_type with parser
            proc add_node_child with result_list, param_type

            Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
            If comma_check is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after return types"
        Return result_list
    End If

    Note: Single return type
    Return proc parse_type with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single struct field declaration 'Name Type [tag]'. Embedded
fields (a bare type as a field) are NOT handled here as a distinct
form - the HIR layer can detect them by inspecting the resulting
node's missing name slot.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the field name lexeme and consumes the identifier. Calls
parse_type for the field type and attaches as child. If the next
token is a string literal (the back-tick tag), consumes it and
records it via set_node_value. Optional semicolon consumed if
present.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_struct_field" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse struct field declaration

    Let field_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FIELD
    Let field_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with field_node, field_name

    Let field_type be proc parse_type with parser
    proc add_node_child with field_node, field_type

    Note: Optional field tag
    Let tag_check be proc check_token_type with parser, TOKEN_STRING from Lexer
    If tag_check is equal to 1:
        Let tag_value be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_attribute with field_node, "tag", tag_value
    End If

    Note: Expect semicolon or newline
    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return field_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single interface method signature 'Name(params) ReturnType'.
Embedded interfaces (a bare interface name listed inside the body)
appear as a method with no parameter list; the parser produces them
with no children of GO_PARAMETER kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads identifier name. If next token is '(' enters method-signature
path: parse_parameter_list, expect ')', optionally parse_type_or_result_list
for the return clause. Otherwise the identifier is an embedded
interface name with no parameters.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_interface_method" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse interface method declaration

    Let method_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FIELD
    Let method_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with method_node, method_name

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after method name"
    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_node_child with method_node, params
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after parameters"

    Note: Return type(s)
    Let next_token be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_token is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        If next_token is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Let return_type be proc parse_type_or_result_list with parser
            proc add_node_child with method_node, return_type
        End If
    End If

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return method_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a comma-separated parameter list (without the surrounding
parentheses - the caller owns those). Empty lists are valid and
yield a fresh List with no children. Trailing commas (Go-1.18 grammar
relaxation) are accepted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops while the cursor is not ')'. Each iteration calls parse_parameter
and appends to the result list. Consumes optional comma between
adjacent entries.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_parameter_list" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse function parameter list

    Let param_list be proc create_go_node with GO_PARAMETER
    proc set_node_name with param_list, "parameters"

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let param be proc parse_parameter with parser
        proc add_node_child with param_list, param

        Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If comma_check is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    Return param_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single parameter 'Name Type' or just 'Type' (anonymous).
The leading identifier is read first; if the next token is itself a
type-introducer the leading identifier was a name; otherwise it was
itself a type identifier (basic type).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the leading identifier. Inspects the next token. If it looks
like a type (identifier, '*', '[', 'chan', 'func', 'map',
'interface', 'struct'), treats the first identifier as the name and
recurses parse_type for the type child. Otherwise treats the
identifier as the type itself (anonymous parameter), creating a
GO_BASIC_TYPE node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_parameter" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse single function parameter

    Let param_node be proc create_go_node with GO_PARAMETER

    Let param_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    Let next_token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Check if this is a type-only parameter
    If next_token_type is not equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let param_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with param_node, param_type
        Return param_node
    End If

    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with param_node, param_name

    Set param_type to proc parse_type with parser
    proc add_node_child with param_node, param_type

    Return param_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statement Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement-level dispatcher. Routes by current token: '{' block,
'if'/'for'/'switch'/'select' control flow, 'return'/'break'/
'continue'/'fallthrough'/'goto' control transfers, 'defer'/'go'
concurrency, 'var'/'const'/'type' nested declarations, fallback to
parse_simple_statement (assignment / short var / expression
statement).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peek token; cascade through token-type equality tests calling the
matching parse_* and returning its result. Default falls into
parse_simple_statement which itself dispatches on the expression
shape (assignment-vs-bare-expr).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse Go statement

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Block statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_block with parser
    End If

    Note: Return statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RETURN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let return_node be proc create_go_node with GO_RETURN_STMT

        Note: Parse return values
        Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
            If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
                Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc add_node_child with return_node, expr

                Note: Multiple return values
                While 1 is equal to 1:
                    Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
                    If comma_check is equal to 0:
                        Break
                    End If

                    Let next_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
                    proc add_node_child with return_node, next_expr
                End While
            End If
        End If

        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return return_node
    End If

    Note: Break statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BREAK from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let break_node be proc create_go_node with GO_BREAK_STMT
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return break_node
    End If

    Note: Continue statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONTINUE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let continue_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CONTINUE_STMT
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return continue_node
    End If

    Note: Fallthrough statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FALLTHROUGH from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let fallthrough_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FALLTHROUGH_STMT
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return fallthrough_node
    End If

    Note: Goto statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GOTO from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let goto_node be proc create_go_node with GO_GOTO_STMT
        Let label_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_name with goto_node, label_name
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return goto_node
    End If

    Note: Defer statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DEFER from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let defer_node be proc create_go_node with GO_DEFER_STMT
        Let call_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with defer_node, call_expr
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return defer_node
    End If

    Note: Go statement (goroutine)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GO from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let go_node be proc create_go_node with GO_GO_STMT
        Set call_expr to proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with go_node, call_expr
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return go_node
    End If

    Note: If statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IF from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_if_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: For statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_for_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Switch statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_switch_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Select statement
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SELECT from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_select_statement with parser
    End If

    Note: Variable declaration
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VAR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_var_declaration with parser
    End If

    Note: Constant declaration
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_const_declaration with parser
    End If

    Note: Type declaration
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPE from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_type_declaration with parser
    End If

    Note: Expression statement, assignment, or short variable declaration
    Return proc parse_simple_statement with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a brace-delimited block '{ statements... }'. Body statements
are accumulated as children of a GO_BLOCK node. Optional trailing
semicolons after statements are consumed silently.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects '{'. Loops while next token is not '}': parse_statement and
add as child. Consumes optional ';'. Expects '}'. Returns the
GO_BLOCK node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_block" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse block statement

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' to start block"

    Let block_node be proc create_go_node with GO_BLOCK

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        proc add_node_child with block_node, stmt
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end block"

    Return block_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Go's 'if [init;] cond { then } [else if ...] [else { ... }]'.
The optional init clause is a simple statement that runs before the
condition and is scoped to the if. The else chain is recursively
parsed when 'else if' appears so the AST stays a tree rather than
flattening into an arbitrary list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'if'. Attempts to parse a simple statement; if followed by
';' treats it as init and parses the condition next; otherwise
treats the parsed expression as the condition directly. Parses the
then-branch as a block. If 'else' follows: 'else if' recurses
parse_if_statement; 'else {' parses another block; 'else stmt' is
not supported (Go requires a block).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_if_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse if statement

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IF from Lexer, "Expected 'if'"

    Let if_node be proc create_go_node with GO_IF_STMT

    Note: Optional init statement
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let init_or_cond be proc parse_simple_statement with parser
        Let semicolon_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

        If semicolon_check is equal to 1:
            Note: This was init statement, parse condition
            proc add_node_child with if_node, init_or_cond
            Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with if_node, condition

        Otherwise:
            Note: This was the condition
            proc add_node_child with if_node, init_or_cond
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse then block
    Let then_block be proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_node_child with if_node, then_block

    Note: Optional else clause
    Let else_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_ELSE from Lexer
    If else_check is equal to 1:
        Let next_type2 be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If next_type2 is equal to TOKEN_IF from Lexer:
            Note: else if
            Let else_if be proc parse_if_statement with parser
            proc add_node_child with if_node, else_if

        Otherwise:
            Note: else block
            Let else_block be proc parse_block with parser
            proc add_node_child with if_node, else_block
        End If
    End If

    Return if_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Go's three loop syntaxes: condition-only 'for cond { ... }',
three-part 'for init; cond; post { ... }', and range form 'for
k, v := range expr { ... }'. The bare 'for { ... }' (infinite loop)
is the condition-only form with no condition.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'for'. If next token is '{' creates a loop_type "infinite"
node. Otherwise parses up to the first semicolon or 'range' keyword
to determine the shape. Range form: parse the assignment target
(simple_statement), expect 'range', parse iterable expression.
Three-part form: parse init simple-statement, ';', condition, ';',
post simple-statement. Condition-only form: just parse condition.
Then parses the body block.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_for_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse for statement (includes for, for range, infinite loop)

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_FOR from Lexer, "Expected 'for'"

    Let for_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FOR_STMT

    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Infinite loop (for { ... })
    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_node_child with for_node, body
        Return for_node
    End If

    Note: Parse init/condition/post or range
    Let first_part be proc parse_simple_statement with parser
    Let next_token be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: For range (for k, v := range x { ... })
    If next_token is equal to TOKEN_RANGE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_attribute with for_node, "type", "range"
        proc add_node_child with for_node, first_part  Note: variables
        Let range_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with for_node, range_expr
        Set body to proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_node_child with for_node, body
        Return for_node
    End If

    Note: Three-part for (for init; condition; post { ... })
    Let semicolon_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    If semicolon_check is equal to 1:
        proc add_node_child with for_node, first_part  Note: init

        Let next_type2 be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If next_type2 is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
            Let condition be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with for_node, condition
        End If

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer, "Expected ';' after condition"

        Let next_type3 be proc peek_token_type with parser
        If next_type3 is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
            Let post_stmt be proc parse_simple_statement with parser
            proc add_node_child with for_node, post_stmt
        End If

        Set body to proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_node_child with for_node, body
        Return for_node
    End If

    Note: Condition-only for (for condition { ... })
    proc add_node_child with for_node, first_part  Note: condition
    Set body to proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_node_child with for_node, body
    Return for_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Go's 'switch [init;] [tag] { case-clauses }'. The init and
tag clauses are both optional; the bare 'switch { ... }' is the
chained-if form. Type switches ('x := y.(type)') are recognised by
inspecting the tag's expression shape - the result is the same
GO_SWITCH node with the type-switch flag set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'switch'. Speculatively parses init/tag with semicolon
detection. Expects '{'. Loops parse_case_clause until '}'. Returns
the populated GO_SWITCH node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_switch_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse switch statement

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_SWITCH from Lexer, "Expected 'switch'"

    Let switch_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SWITCH_STMT

    Note: Optional init statement and tag
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let init_or_tag be proc parse_simple_statement with parser
        Let semicolon_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

        If semicolon_check is equal to 1:
            Note: This was init statement, parse tag
            proc add_node_child with switch_node, init_or_tag
            Let tag be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with switch_node, tag

        Otherwise:
            Note: This was the tag
            proc add_node_child with switch_node, init_or_tag
        End If
    End If

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' after switch"

    Note: Parse case clauses
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let case_clause be proc parse_case_clause with parser
        proc add_node_child with switch_node, case_clause
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end switch"

    Return switch_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Go's 'select { case-clauses }', the channel-multiplexing
statement. Cases are either communication operations or 'default',
parsed by the same parse_case_clause as switch.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'select'. Expects '{'. Loops parse_case_clause until '}'.
Returns the GO_SELECT node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_select_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse select statement

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_SELECT from Lexer, "Expected 'select'"

    Let select_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SELECT_STMT

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' after select"

    Note: Parse case clauses
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let case_clause be proc parse_case_clause with parser
        proc add_node_child with select_node, case_clause
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end select"

    Return select_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single case or default clause for switch/select. 'case' is
followed by one or more comma-separated expressions (for switch) or
a single communication operation (for select); 'default' has no
header expression. The body is a sequence of statements without
braces, terminated by the next 'case'/'default'/'}'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'case' or 'default'. For 'case' parses a comma-separated
expression list and attaches as children. For 'default' marks the
node via set_node_attribute("is_default", "true"). Expects ':'.
Loops parsing statements while the next token is not 'case',
'default', or '}'. Returns the GO_CASE_CLAUSE node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_case_clause" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse case or default clause

    Let case_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CASE_CLAUSE
    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CASE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser

        Note: Parse case expressions
        Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with case_node, expr

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
            If comma_check is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If

            Let next_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with case_node, next_expr
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer, "Expected ':' after case"
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DEFAULT from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_attribute with case_node, "default", "true"
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer, "Expected ':' after default"
    End If

    Note: Parse case body statements
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If next_type is equal to TOKEN_CASE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        If next_type is equal to TOKEN_DEFAULT from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        If next_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser
        proc add_node_child with case_node, stmt
    End While

    Return case_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Go's "simple statement" - the subset that may appear as the
init/post of if/for, including assignments, short var decls, and
plain expression statements. Discrimination among the three forms is
done by inspecting the token after the first expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses an expression. If followed by '=' produces a GO_ASSIGN with
right-hand expression. If followed by ':=' produces a
GO_SHORT_VAR_DECL with values. If followed by a compound assign
('+=', '-=', etc.) produces a GO_ASSIGN with operator attribute.
Otherwise the expression itself becomes a GO_EXPR_STMT wrapper.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_simple_statement" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse simple statement (assignment, short var decl, expression)

    Note: Parse the (possibly comma-separated) left-hand side. Go permits
    Note: multiple targets in both short declarations (`i, v := range xs`,
    Note: `q, r := f()`) and assignments (`a, b = b, a`). The first target
    Note: is stored at children[0] and any additional targets follow it,
    Note: before the right-hand side expressions are appended.
    Let left_expr be proc parse_expression with parser

    Let extra_lhs be proc create from List
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let lhs_comma be proc check_token_type with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If lhs_comma is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let next_lhs be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc list_append from List with extra_lhs, next_lhs
    End While
    Let extra_lhs_count be proc length from List with extra_lhs

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Short variable declaration (:=)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_COLON_EQUAL from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let short_decl_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SHORT_VAR_DECL
        proc add_node_child with short_decl_node, left_expr
        Let li be 0
        While li is less than extra_lhs_count:
            Let lt be proc get from List with extra_lhs, li
            proc add_node_child with short_decl_node, lt
            Set li to li plus 1
        End While

        Let right_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with short_decl_node, right_expr
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let rhs_comma be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
            If rhs_comma is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
            Let next_rhs be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with short_decl_node, next_rhs
        End While

        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return short_decl_node
    End If

    Note: Assignment (=, +=, -=, etc.)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let assign_node be proc create_go_node with GO_ASSIGN_STMT
        proc set_node_attribute with assign_node, "operator", "="
        proc add_node_child with assign_node, left_expr
        Let ali be 0
        While ali is less than extra_lhs_count:
            Let alt be proc get from List with extra_lhs, ali
            proc add_node_child with assign_node, alt
            Set ali to ali plus 1
        End While

        Set right_expr to proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with assign_node, right_expr
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Set rhs_comma to proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
            If rhs_comma is equal to 0:
                Break
            End If
            Set next_rhs to proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with assign_node, next_rhs
        End While

        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return assign_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS_EQUAL from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set assign_node to proc create_go_node with GO_ASSIGN_STMT
        proc set_node_attribute with assign_node, "operator", "+="
        proc add_node_child with assign_node, left_expr
        Set right_expr to proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with assign_node, right_expr
        proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
        Return assign_node
    End If

    Note: Expression statement (single expression; no comma list applies)
    Let expr_stmt_node be proc create_go_node with GO_EXPR_STMT
    proc add_node_child with expr_stmt_node, left_expr
    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    Return expr_stmt_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'var SPEC' or grouped 'var ( SPECS... )'. Each spec carries
a name(s), optional type, and optional initialiser. The grouped
form lets multiple specs share the 'var' keyword.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'var'. Peeks for '('; if grouped form, loops parse_var_spec
appending each as a child of a GO_VAR_DECL node, terminating on
')'. Otherwise calls parse_var_spec once and attaches as child.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_var_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse variable declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_VAR from Lexer, "Expected 'var'"

    Let var_node be proc create_go_node with GO_VAR_DECL

    Note: Single variable or block
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Variable block
        proc advance_token with parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let var_spec be proc parse_var_spec with parser
            proc add_node_child with var_node, var_spec
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' to end var block"

    Otherwise:
        Note: Single variable
        Set var_spec to proc parse_var_spec with parser
        proc add_node_child with var_node, var_spec
    End If

    Return var_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single var spec 'Names Type = Values' (any of type/values
may be absent if the other is present). Multiple comma-separated
names are permitted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads a comma-separated list of identifiers. If a type-introducing
token follows, calls parse_type. If '=' follows, parses a comma-
separated list of initialiser expressions. Returns a GO_VAR_SPEC
node with names, optional type, and optional values as children.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_var_spec" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse variable specification

    Let var_spec_node be proc create_go_node with GO_VAR_DECL
    Let var_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with var_spec_node, var_name

    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Type specified
    If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Let var_type be proc parse_type with parser
        proc add_node_child with var_spec_node, var_type
        Let next_type2 be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If next_type2 is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let init_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with var_spec_node, init_expr
        End If

    Otherwise:
        Note: Type inferred from initializer
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set init_expr to proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with var_spec_node, init_expr
    End If

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    Return var_spec_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'const SPEC' or grouped 'const ( SPECS... )'. Mirrors
parse_var_declaration but the spec form requires an initialiser
(verified by the type-checker, not the parser).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'const'. Peeks for '('; loops parse_const_spec in grouped
form, otherwise single-shot. Attaches specs to a GO_CONST_DECL node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_const_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse constant declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_CONST from Lexer, "Expected 'const'"

    Let const_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CONST_DECL

    Note: Single constant or block
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Constant block
        proc advance_token with parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let const_spec be proc parse_const_spec with parser
            proc add_node_child with const_node, const_spec
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' to end const block"

    Otherwise:
        Note: Single constant
        Set const_spec to proc parse_const_spec with parser
        proc add_node_child with const_node, const_spec
    End If

    Return const_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a single const spec 'Names [Type] = Values'. Within a grouped
const block, a spec may omit '= Values' (and reuse the previous
spec's initialiser via iota); this parser captures the spec as-is
and leaves the iota interpretation to a later pass.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads names list. Optional type. If '=' follows, parses comma-
separated value expressions. Returns GO_CONST_SPEC node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_const_spec" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse constant specification

    Let const_spec_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CONST_DECL
    Let const_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with const_spec_node, const_name

    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Type specified (optional for constants)
    If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer:
        If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
            Let const_type be proc parse_type with parser
            proc add_node_child with const_spec_node, const_type
        End If
    End If

    Note: Constant value
    Let equal_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer
    If equal_check is equal to 1:
        Let value_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with const_spec_node, value_expr
    End If

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    Return const_spec_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'type SPEC' or grouped 'type ( SPECS... )'. Each spec is a
'Name Type' or 'Name = Type' (type alias, since Go 1.9).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'type'. Peek for '('; loops parse_type_spec in grouped
form, otherwise single-shot. Attaches specs to a GO_TYPE_DECL node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_TYPE from Lexer, "Expected 'type'"

    Let type_decl_node be proc create_go_node with GO_TYPE_DECL

    Note: Single type or block
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        Note: Type block
        proc advance_token with parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let type_spec be proc parse_type_spec with parser
            proc add_node_child with type_decl_node, type_spec
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' to end type block"

    Otherwise:
        Note: Single type
        Set type_spec to proc parse_type_spec with parser
        proc add_node_child with type_decl_node, type_spec
    End If

    Return type_decl_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'Name Type' or 'Name = Type' (alias). The presence of '='
distinguishes new-type declarations from aliases; the parser records
the alias flag via set_node_attribute("is_alias", "true").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads name identifier. If '=' follows, consumes it and records the
alias flag. Calls parse_type for the definition. Returns GO_TYPE_SPEC
node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_spec" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse type specification

    Let type_spec_node be proc create_go_node with GO_TYPE_DECL
    Let type_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with type_spec_node, type_name

    Let underlying_type be proc parse_type with parser
    proc add_node_child with type_spec_node, underlying_type

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer
    Return type_spec_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level expression entry. Delegates to the Pratt-style precedence
parser parse_binary_expression with the lowest precedence (1) so
all operators bind freely from the start.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tail-calls parse_binary_expression(parser, 1).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse expression with operator precedence

    Note: The lowest real binary-operator precedence is 1 (Go's '||'), so
    Note: parsing must start at min_precedence 1. get_operator_precedence
    Note: returns 0 for any non-operator token; starting at 1 makes the
    Note: precedence-climbing loop terminate on the first non-operator
    Note: (0 < 1) instead of treating it as a zero-precedence operator and
    Note: looping forever.
    Return proc parse_binary_expression with parser, 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Precedence-climbing parser for Go's left-associative binary
operators. Parses a unary operand, then loops consuming operators
whose precedence is >= min_precedence; for each such operator
recursively parses the right operand with min_precedence = current
op's precedence + 1 (left-associative).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls parse_unary_expression for the left operand. Loop: read
peek_token_type, ask get_operator_precedence; if < min_precedence
break. Otherwise consume the operator, recursively call
parse_binary_expression with prec+1, construct a GO_BINARY_EXPR with
the captured operator and (left, right) children. Replace left with
the new node and continue. Returns the accumulated left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_binary_expression" takes parser as Integer, min_precedence as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse binary expression with precedence climbing

    Let left be proc parse_unary_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
        Let precedence be proc get_operator_precedence with token_type

        If precedence is less than min_precedence:
            Break
        End If

        Let operator be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser

        Let right be proc parse_binary_expression with parser, precedence plus 1

        Let binary_node be proc create_go_node with GO_BINARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with binary_node, operator
        proc add_node_child with binary_node, left
        proc add_node_child with binary_node, right

        Set left to binary_node
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns Go's binary operator precedence (1..5, higher binds tighter).
The Go spec defines exactly five precedence levels:
  5: '*' '/' '%' '<<' '>>' '&' '&^'
  4: '+' '-' '|' '^'
  3: '==' '!=' '<' '<=' '>' '>='
  2: '&&'
  1: '||'
Non-operator tokens return 0 so parse_binary_expression can detect
loop termination.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Cascade of equality tests against TOKEN_* operator constants, each
returning the appropriate precedence. Falls through to 0 for any
unrecognised token type.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_operator_precedence" takes token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get operator precedence (higher = tighter binding)

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE_PIPE from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMP_AMP from Lexer:
        Return 2
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 3
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BANG_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 3
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        Return 4
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LESS_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 4
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
        Return 4
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GREATER_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 4
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer:
        Return 5
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
        Return 5
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE from Lexer:
        Return 5
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET from Lexer:
        Return 5
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SLASH from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LSHIFT from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RSHIFT from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMP_CARET from Lexer:
        Return 6
    End If

    Return 0  Note: Not a binary operator
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Go unary expression. Operators: '+', '-', '!', '^'
(complement), '*' (deref), '&' (address-of), '<-' (channel
receive). After consuming the operator the operand is parsed with
parse_unary_expression itself (allowing nested unary stacks like
'!!x'); falls through to parse_postfix_expression for non-unary
expressions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peek; if operator token is a unary prefix, consume it; recurse
parse_unary_expression for operand; wrap in GO_UNARY_EXPR with
operator and operand. Otherwise delegate to parse_postfix_expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_unary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse unary expression

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Unary operators
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let unary_node be proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "+"
        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "-"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BANG from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "!"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "^"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STAR from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "*"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMP from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "&"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ARROW from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
        proc set_node_name with unary_node, "<-"
        Set operand to proc parse_unary_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with unary_node, operand
        Return unary_node
    End If

    Return proc parse_postfix_expression with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles left-recursive postfix operations on a primary expression:
call '(args)', index '[i]', slice '[lo:hi[:max]]', selector '.name',
and type assertion '.(Type)'. Each operation wraps the running expr
in a new node; the loop continues until no more postfix tokens are
present.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Calls parse_primary_expression for the base. Loop: peek token.
  '(' -> consume; comma-separated argument list (each via
         parse_expression); expect ')'; wrap as GO_CALL_EXPR with
         callee + args.
  '[' -> consume; parse low expression. If next is ':' parse slice
         (handles two- and three-index forms). Otherwise expect ']'
         and wrap as GO_INDEX_EXPR.
  '.' -> consume; if next is '(' it's a type assertion: parse_type,
         ')', wrap GO_TYPE_ASSERT_EXPR. Else read identifier and
         wrap as GO_SELECTOR_EXPR.
  Anything else terminates the loop.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_postfix_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse postfix expression (calls, indexing, selectors, etc.)

    Let expr be proc parse_primary_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        Note: Function call
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let call_node be proc create_go_node with GO_CALL_EXPR
            proc add_node_child with call_node, expr

            Note: Parse arguments
            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

                If next_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                    Break
                End If

                Let arg be proc parse_expression with parser
                proc add_node_child with call_node, arg

                Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
                If comma_check is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
            End While

            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after arguments"
            Set expr to call_node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Indexing
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let index_node be proc create_go_node with GO_INDEX_EXPR
            proc add_node_child with index_node, expr

            Let index_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
            proc add_node_child with index_node, index_expr

            Note: Check for slice (x[low:high])
            Let colon_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer
            If colon_check is equal to 1:
                Let slice_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SLICE_EXPR
                proc add_node_child with slice_node, expr
                proc add_node_child with slice_node, index_expr

                Set next_type to proc peek_token_type with parser
                If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer:
                    Let high_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
                    proc add_node_child with slice_node, high_expr
                End If

                proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer, "Expected ']' after slice"
                Set expr to slice_node
                Continue
            End If

            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACKET from Lexer, "Expected ']' after index"
            Set expr to index_node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Selector (x.y)
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DOT from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let selector_node be proc create_go_node with GO_SELECTOR_EXPR
            proc add_node_child with selector_node, expr

            Let field_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
            proc advance_token with parser

            Let field_node be proc create_go_node with GO_IDENTIFIER
            proc set_node_name with field_node, field_name
            proc add_node_child with selector_node, field_node

            Note: Check for type assertion (x.(T))
            Let lparen_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer
            If lparen_check is equal to 1:
                Let assert_node be proc create_go_node with GO_TYPE_ASSERT_EXPR
                proc add_node_child with assert_node, expr
                Let assert_type be proc parse_type with parser
                proc add_node_child with assert_node, assert_type
                proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after type assertion"
                Set expr to assert_node
                Continue
            End If

            Set expr to selector_node
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Increment/decrement
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS_PLUS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Let unary_node be proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
            proc set_node_name with unary_node, "++"
            proc add_node_child with unary_node, expr
            Set expr to unary_node
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS_MINUS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token with parser
            Set unary_node to proc create_go_node with GO_UNARY_EXPR
            proc set_node_name with unary_node, "--"
            proc add_node_child with unary_node, expr
            Set expr to unary_node
            Continue
        End If

        Break
    End While

    Return expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses the smallest indivisible expression units: identifiers,
literals, parenthesised expressions, composite literals (Type{...}),
function literals (func(...) {...}), and type-conversion call forms.
Postfix operations are layered on by parse_postfix_expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads peek_token_type. Cases:
  TOKEN_IDENTIFIER -> read lexeme into GO_IDENTIFIER node; if
                      followed by '{' upgrades to composite literal.
  TOKEN_INTEGER/FLOAT/STRING/CHAR -> wraps in GO_LITERAL with the
                                     lexeme as value.
  TOKEN_LPAREN -> consume, parse_expression, expect ')'.
  TOKEN_FUNC -> parse_function_literal.
  Type-introducing tokens (chan, map, struct, etc.) -> parse_type;
  if followed by '{' becomes composite literal.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_primary_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse primary expression (literals, identifiers, parenthesized)

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Literals
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from Lexer:
        Let value be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let literal_node be proc create_go_node with GO_LITERAL
        proc set_node_name with literal_node, "integer"
        proc set_node_value with literal_node, value
        Return literal_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FLOAT from Lexer:
        Set value to proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set literal_node to proc create_go_node with GO_LITERAL
        proc set_node_name with literal_node, "float"
        proc set_node_value with literal_node, value
        Return literal_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRING from Lexer:
        Set value to proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set literal_node to proc create_go_node with GO_LITERAL
        proc set_node_name with literal_node, "string"
        proc set_node_value with literal_node, value
        Return literal_node
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RUNE from Lexer:
        Set value to proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Set literal_node to proc create_go_node with GO_LITERAL
        proc set_node_name with literal_node, "rune"
        proc set_node_value with literal_node, value
        Return literal_node
    End If

    Note: Identifier
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let id_node be proc create_go_node with GO_IDENTIFIER
        proc set_node_name with id_node, name
        Return id_node
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized expression
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let inner_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after expression"
        Return inner_expr
    End If

    Note: Composite literal or function literal
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FUNC from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_function_literal with parser
    End If

    Note: Type-prefixed composite literal: []T{...}, [N]T{...},
    Note: map[K]V{...}, struct{...}{...}. These begin with a type-
    Note: introducing token and are unambiguous (unlike Ident{...},
    Note: which collides with control-statement block braces).
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_type_prefixed_composite with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MAP from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_type_prefixed_composite with parser
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_type_prefixed_composite with parser
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a type-prefixed composite literal `TYPE{ elements }` where TYPE
is a slice, array, map, or struct type. The type is parsed via
parse_type, then a '{'-delimited element list follows. Each element is
either a bare value expression or a `key: value` pair; the pair is
represented as a GO_BINARY_EXPR carrying the ':' operator so the
existing expression machinery (translation + emission) round-trips the
key/value spelling without a dedicated node kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
parse_type yields the composite's type node, attached as the first
child of a GO_COMPOSITE_LIT. expect '{'. Loop until '}': parse an
element via parse_expression; if the next token is ':' consume it,
parse the value expression, and wrap key+value in a GO_BINARY_EXPR
node named ":". Append each element as a child. Commas separate
elements; a trailing comma before '}' is permitted. expect '}'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_type_prefixed_composite" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a type-prefixed composite literal TYPE{ elements }

    Let composite_node be proc create_go_node with GO_COMPOSITE_LIT

    Let type_node be proc parse_type with parser
    proc add_node_child with composite_node, type_node

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' after composite literal type"

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let element be proc parse_expression with parser

        Note: Keyed element (key: value) -> GO_BINARY_EXPR named ':'
        Let colon_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer
        If colon_check is equal to 1:
            Let value_expr be proc parse_expression with parser
            Let pair_node be proc create_go_node with GO_BINARY_EXPR
            proc set_node_name with pair_node, ":"
            proc add_node_child with pair_node, element
            proc add_node_child with pair_node, value_expr
            proc add_node_child with composite_node, pair_node
        Otherwise:
            proc add_node_child with composite_node, element
        End If

        Let comma_check be proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer
        If comma_check is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
    End While

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '}' to end composite literal"

    Return composite_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'func(params) ret { body }' as an expression value (anonymous
function). Used inside go-routine launches, defer payloads, and
callback arguments.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'func'. Expects '('; parse_parameter_list; expects ')'.
Optionally parses return type via parse_type_or_result_list. Parses
the body via parse_block. Returns a GO_FUNC_LIT node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_function_literal" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse function literal (anonymous function)

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_FUNC from Lexer, "Expected 'func'"

    Let func_lit_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FUNC_LIT

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after 'func'"
    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_node_child with func_lit_node, params
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after parameters"

    Note: Return type(s)
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_type is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let return_type be proc parse_type_or_result_list with parser
        proc add_node_child with func_lit_node, return_type
    End If

    Let body be proc parse_block with parser
    proc add_node_child with func_lit_node, body

    Return func_lit_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Declaration Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a top-level 'func [(recv)] Name(params) ret { body }'. The
optional receiver clause between 'func' and the name turns this into
a method declaration; both forms collapse onto the same GO_FUNC_DECL
node with an optional receiver child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'func'. If next token is '(' parses a receiver parameter
(within parens) and attaches as a child marked via
set_node_attribute("receiver", "true"). Reads function name.
parse_parameter_list. Optional return type. parse_block on body.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_function_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse function declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_FUNC from Lexer, "Expected 'func'"

    Let func_node be proc create_go_node with GO_FUNCTION

    Note: Check for receiver (method)
    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        Let receiver be proc parse_parameter with parser
        proc set_node_attribute with func_node, "receiver", receiver
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after receiver"
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with func_node, 0, GO_METHOD  Note: Change to method
    End If

    Let func_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc advance_token with parser
    proc set_node_name with func_node, func_name

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer, "Expected '(' after function name"
    Let params be proc parse_parameter_list with parser
    proc add_node_child with func_node, params
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' after parameters"

    Note: Return type(s)
    Let next_type2 be proc peek_token_type with parser
    If next_type2 is not equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer:
        Let return_type be proc parse_type_or_result_list with parser
        proc add_node_child with func_node, return_type
    End If

    Note: Function body (optional for external declarations)
    Let body_check be proc check_token_type with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer
    If body_check is equal to 1:
        Let body be proc parse_block with parser
        proc add_node_child with func_node, body
    End If

    Return func_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'import SPEC' or grouped 'import ( SPECS... )'. Each spec is
an optional alias plus a quoted path string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Consumes 'import'. Peek for '('; in grouped form loops
parse_import_spec until ')'; otherwise single-shot. Attaches specs
to a GO_IMPORT_DECL node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_import_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse import declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IMPORT from Lexer, "Expected 'import'"

    Let import_node be proc create_go_node with GO_IMPORT

    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Import block
    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer:
                Break
            End If

            Let import_spec be proc parse_import_spec with parser
            proc add_node_child with import_node, import_spec
        End While

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_RPAREN from Lexer, "Expected ')' to end import block"

    Otherwise:
        Note: Single import
        Set import_spec to proc parse_import_spec with parser
        proc add_node_child with import_node, import_spec
    End If

    Return import_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'ALIAS? "path"'. The alias may be '.' (dot import - brings
identifiers into local scope) or '_' (blank import - for side
effects only) or a regular identifier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks for an alias prefix (TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, TOKEN_DOT, or
TOKEN_UNDERSCORE); consumes if present and records via set_node_name.
Expects a string literal for the path; consumes it and records via
set_node_value. Returns a GO_IMPORT_SPEC node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_import_spec" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse import specification

    Let import_spec_node be proc create_go_node with GO_IMPORT

    Let next_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

    Note: Check for alias or dot import
    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let alias be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_name with import_spec_node, alias
    End If

    If next_type is equal to TOKEN_DOT from Lexer:
        proc advance_token with parser
        proc set_node_attribute with import_spec_node, "dot_import", "true"
    End If

    Let path be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_STRING from Lexer, "Expected import path string"
    proc set_node_value with import_spec_node, path

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return import_spec_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses 'package NAME', which Go requires as the very first statement
of every source file. The package name is captured but not validated
(the linker checks consistency across files).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects 'package'. Reads identifier as package name and stores via
set_node_name on a new GO_PACKAGE node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_package_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse package declaration

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_PACKAGE from Lexer, "Expected 'package'"

    Let package_node be proc create_go_node with GO_PACKAGE
    Let package_name be proc peek_token_lexeme with parser

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer, "Expected package name"
    proc set_node_name with package_node, package_name

    proc match_token with parser, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer

    Return package_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Parser Entry
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry. A Go source file is exactly: a package clause, then
a sequence of import declarations, then a sequence of top-level
declarations (function, method, var, const, type). The order is
enforced lexically here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a GO_PROGRAM root. Calls parse_package_declaration and
attaches. Loops: while peek is 'import' call parse_import_declaration.
Loops: while not EOF, dispatch on peek - 'func' ->
parse_function_declaration; 'var' -> parse_var_declaration; 'const'
-> parse_const_declaration; 'type' -> parse_type_declaration;
anything else is an error and ends the parse. Returns the populated
GO_PROGRAM node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_program" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse complete Go program

    Let program_node be proc create_go_node with GO_PROGRAM

    Note: Parse package declaration
    Let package_decl be proc parse_package_declaration with parser
    proc add_node_child with program_node, package_decl

    Note: Parse imports
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_IMPORT from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Let import_decl be proc parse_import_declaration with parser
        proc add_node_child with program_node, import_decl
    End While

    Note: Parse top-level declarations
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Set token_type to proc peek_token_type with parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FUNC from Lexer:
            Let func_decl be proc parse_function_declaration with parser
            proc add_node_child with program_node, func_decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPE from Lexer:
            Let type_decl be proc parse_type_declaration with parser
            proc add_node_child with program_node, type_decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_VAR from Lexer:
            Let var_decl be proc parse_var_declaration with parser
            proc add_node_child with program_node, var_decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CONST from Lexer:
            Let const_decl be proc parse_const_declaration with parser
            proc add_node_child with program_node, const_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Unknown token - skip
        proc advance_token with parser
    End While

    Return program_node
End Process
